/target

# Rust build lockfile — this crate is a library, so we do
# not commit Cargo.lock. See https://doc.rust-lang.org/cargo/faq.html#why-do-binaries-have-cargolock-in-version-control-but-not-libraries
Cargo.lock

# cargo-fuzz build + crash artifacts. The corpus directory is CI-cached
# (not committed) except for the hand-placed `seed-*` starter inputs.
fuzz/target/
fuzz/artifacts/
fuzz/coverage/
fuzz/corpus/**
!fuzz/corpus/*/
!fuzz/corpus/*/seed-*
